  <h1 class="page-title">Exaile Support Resources</h1>
  <p>If you believe you have found a bug, you can click <a href="https://github.com/exaile/exaile/issues/new">here</a> to report it.  You will need to create a github account before you can post a bug report.</p>

<p>You may want to check the <a href="http://exaile.readthedocs.org/en/latest/user/faq.html">Frequently Asked Questions</a> to see if your question is addressed there. Otherwise, the following ways are available to get support or ask questions you might have about using or developing Exaile:</p>

<p><strong>MAILING LISTS</strong></p>

<p>We run mailing lists for various purposes.</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><a href="http://groups.google.com/group/exaile-users">exaile-users</a> - A list for people who use Exaile. Open to discussion between users to communicate and help each other.  If you’re having trouble using Exaile, ask here.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="http://groups.google.com/group/exaile-devel">exaile-devel</a> - Our primary list for general development discussion. Questions about the code, plugin development, packaging, etc. should go here.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p><strong>IRC</strong></p>

<p>Exaile developers can be reached on <strong>#exaile</strong> channel on <a href="http://freenode.net/irc_servers.shtml">Freenode</a>. <em>Note: the channel is not very active, but if you stick around long enough someone will probably answer your question – think in terms of email response time</em></p>

